Reasoning: 
- cs.ET (Emerging Technologies): The paper discusses the computational power of real-time probabilistic and quantum computers, which can be considered as emerging technologies in computer science.
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity): The paper examines the language classes recognized by finite automata with postselection, which is a topic related to computational complexity.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms): The paper proposes a new model of finite automata with postselection, which can be seen as a data structure or algorithmic technique.
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science): The paper establishes separations between different modes of recognition in the model of finite automata with postselection, which involves logical reasoning.
- cs.PL (Programming Languages): The paper introduces a new model of computation and compares it with an existing one, which can be seen as a programming language-related topic.
